istrict in NJ - like one of the best in the nation - to an ok district in NC. I did not know one single family who home-schooled back in NJ but I can't even count the number here in NC. I know several on a personal level, but then there are so many more that I meet just casually, like chatting with a mom during our kids' swim lessons. They're everywhere! There seems to be a whole industry set up around it too, with special classes aimed at the home-schooling crowd, at museums, libraries, or sports. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="807" language="en" documentId="504" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Sonderella" date="09/05/2013" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://community.babycenter.com/post/a44369503/home_schooling_debate_this_hypothetical?cpg=12" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="504" notes="" title="Home schooling: Debate this hypothetical"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="112"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="113" end="807"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43"/></xmi:XMI>